# REFERENCE ONLY — env var NAMES, no values, safe in a public repo.
#
# There is NO secret file in this repo (it is open source). Secrets live ONLY
# in the gated `prod` GitHub Environment. `standup.yml` maps each Environment
# secret to one of these ARXII_* env vars ON THE ansible-playbook STEP ONLY;
# the secrets_vault role reads them via lookup('env', ...) and renders the
# 0600 on-box EnvironmentFile. Local-fallback: the operator exports the same
# ARXII_* vars from a password manager (never on the command line).
#
# ON-BOX set (decision 10) — required:
#   ARXII_PG_PASSWORD
#   ARXII_DJANGO_SECRET_KEY
#   ARXII_CLOUDINARY_URL
#   ARXII_RESEND_API_KEY
#   ARXII_BACKUP_WRITER_ACCESS_KEY
#   ARXII_BACKUP_WRITER_SECRET_KEY
#   ARXII_R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID
#   ARXII_R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
#   ARXII_OFFBOX_ALERT_TOKEN
#   ARXII_CADDY_CF_DNS_TOKEN   (Cloudflare DNS-edit-scoped token for Caddy
#                               ACME DNS-01 — distinct from the provisioning
#                               Cloudflare token; bucket... zone-scoped)
#
# MUST NOT be present in the ansible-playbook step's env (operator/CI-only;
# they belong to the tofu step, never on the box):
#   ARXII_LINODE_TOKEN, ARXII_CLOUDFLARE_TOKEN
